                <h2>About <span class="feature-color">Dylan</span></h2>
                <img src="/images/headshpt.png" width=400/>
                <p>
                    Hi, I’m Dylan and I’m running to be the President of your Students’ Union.

                    Over the last year I’ve been working as your VP External where I advocated to all levels of government

                    for things like student jobs, tuition, and mental health funding.

                    I want to make school more affordable, build student community from the ground up, and raise revenue

                    for the SU without increasing fees.

                    University needs to stay affordable and to do that, I will be advocating for an affordable U-Pass in our

                    upcoming negotiations, working with the next VPX to rollback tuition, and lobbying for more student

                    grants.

                    Students build student community. This has been forgotten in past years and to ensure this I will be

                    advocating that Residence Associations be able to collect fees, and control of student groups into the

                    hands of the SU.

                    In my term, I will find ways to increase the revenue of the SU outside fees; this means the development

                    of an alumni endowment fund, filling all retail spaces in SUB, and improving our businesses.

                    Finally, I won’t pretend to know everything you care about, so thats why I am allowing you to add your own idea below or If you just want to chat you can email me at hanwell@ualberta.ca
                </p>
